snippet.textDisplay: Why the Miz hasn't been given another title push is completely beyond me. He's over with the fans as both a heel and a face, he's great on the mic, he puts on really good matches, he knows how to sell a story in the ring and he's really good at putting people over. Plus, he never gets injured. At a time when the WWE are scrambling around to find the next big superstar, they have a legitimate superstar on their roster. It makes no sense to me how Bray Wyatt can flounder around the card for several years, come back, have sub-standard matches and be put into the main event scene, based on a change of gimmick? I can't name one Bray Wyatt match that I've enjoyed from start to finish. The Miz deserves so much more than he gets.
